@startuml
title KHIE Payer Workflow System Context
left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor "Clinical user" as clinician
component "JaliHealth React workflows\n- Outpatient\n- Inpatient\n- ECCIF emergency" as react
component "Medplum Bot runtime\nKHIE workflow handlers" as bots
component "KHIE core client\nFacility resolution\nOAuth token cache\nAPI wrappers" as core
database "Medplum FHIR repository\nPatient, PractitionerRole, Location\nEncounter, Coverage, Claim, Task" as fhir
cloud "KHIE API\nEligibility, claims, preauth\nEmergency, protocol endpoints" as khie
database "KHIE token endpoint" as token

rectangle "JaliHealth / Medplum trust boundary" {
  react
  bots
  core
  fhir
}

clinician --> react : clinical workflow actions
react --> bots : executeBot(input)
bots --> fhir : read / create / update FHIR resources
bots --> core : resolve context and call client
core --> fhir : load facility / role context
core --> token : OAuth client credentials
core --> khie : authenticated REST calls\nfacility headers when configured

note bottom of fhir
Claims persist KHIE consent tokens after a KHIE
authorization or emergency response supplies one.
Tasks retain business status and workflow inputs.
end note

note bottom of core
The resolved facility is selected by precedence:
encounter, patient location, selected location,
role default, organization default.
end note
@enduml